<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Where Beginners Usually Run Into Trouble</h2>

  <h3>Overbuying Equipment</h3>
  <p>
    More tools don’t solve alignment or healing issues.
  </p>

  <h3>Ignoring Clip Fit</h3>
  <p>
    This is one of the most common failure points.
  </p>

  <h3>Underestimating Healing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Dry air or temperature swings can ruin otherwise good grafts.
  </p>

  <h3>Focusing on Tools Instead of Timing</h3>
  <p>
    Seedling size at grafting stage matters more than equipment.
  </p>
